communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Al-Hudaydah (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al_Hudaydah) also known in English as Hodeda, Hodeida, Hudaida, or Hodeidah, is the 4th-largest city in Yemen and its principal port on the Red Sea. It is the centre of the Al Hudaydah governorate.

No specific numbers of new cases is given in this report. The last Yemen cholera situation report (http://www.emro.who.int/yem/yemeninfocus/situation-reports.html) still covers only through 1 Jul 2018. The cumulative data on this prolonged outbreak is:

