The low case fatality rate might suggest that some of the diarrhea may be non-cholera. Although the daily rate has dropped significantly from the same period in 2017, this many new diarrhea cases per day remains substantial. There had been a slowing of cases during the 3-month period of January-March 2017 as well. The daily rate seems to be moving upwards a bit. - Mod.LL

